00:04:44.660 --> 00:04:46.865
In desire, we want an Other,

00:04:46.889 --> 00:04:49.914
somebody on the other side
that we can go visit,

00:04:49.938 --> 00:04:52.096
that we can go spend some time with,

00:04:52.120 --> 00:04:55.265
that we can go see what goes on
in their red-light district.

00:04:55.875 --> 00:04:56.876
You know?

00:04:56.900 --> 00:04:59.269
In desire, we want a bridge to cross.

00:04:59.293 --> 00:05:02.274
Or in other words,
I sometimes say, fire needs air.

00:05:02.668 --> 00:05:04.512
Desire needs space.

00:05:04.989 --> 00:05:08.443
And when it's said like that,
it's often quite abstract.

00:05:08.467 --> 00:05:10.134
But then I took a question with me.

00:05:10.158 --> 00:05:13.063
And I've gone to more than 20 countries
